to open a new repo, you will always need new folder
to create a folder, go to microsoft cmd and then mkdir name 
cd name and then code .
this will take you to the visual studio code
ctrl + shift (before that in GUI create a repo)
then initialize repo by GUI or git init command in visual studio code
select new file option and you are good to go
git add .
git commit -m "comment" .
git push
git status
if upstream is not set up then setup by "git push --set-upstream origin master"
check Gui for edits
